1.	Requirement Summary

Omanair wants to integrate ERP payments with Bank Sohar. Payments will be created in ERP and file will be generated as per the format provided by Bank Sohar and it will be validated, encrypted and transmitted to Bank Sohar through SFTP. 
2.	Solution
1.	Bank Sohar accounts will be maintained in a lookup and payment file will consider only these bank accounts. Business team needs to maintain this lookup (addition/modification/Deletion)
2.	CSV type of payment file will be generated for the Bank Sohar accounts
3.	All the required validations will be done. If there are any issues, payment program log file will display the errors
4.	Once validation is successful, file will be encrypted and sent to the Bank Sohar server using SFTP.
5.	File will be processed by Bank. If approval is needed, Omanair team needs to approve the same in the Bank portal

3.	File Name Structure
<Customer Reference>_<Entity Reference>_<Applicant Reference>_<Accounting Type>_<Processing Type>_<Customers Own File Name>.csv
S. No 	Field Name 	Mandatory /Length 	Remarks 	Comments
1 	Customer Reference 	M 	This value will be customer reference as maintained in the banks system. To be provided by the bank. 	Bank to provide the details
2 	Entity Reference 	M 	This value will be entity (subsidiary) reference as maintained in the banks system. To be provided by the bank. 	Bank to provide the details
3 	Applicant reference 	M 	This value will be applicant reference as maintained in the banks system. To be provided by the bank. 	Bank to provide the details
4 	Accounting Type 	M / 250	2 types of accounting types are supported
1. MDMC
2. SDMC

MDMC – Multiple Debit Multiple Credit will ensure that the transactions in the batch are debited to the customer account one by one 
SDMC – Single Debit Multi Credit will ensure that the customer account is debited with the consolidated amount of the complete batch. Account statement will reflect one single debit entry at a batch level 
For processing salary transactions above 20,000 OMR (per record) this value will be “ SAL” 	MDMC (Business to confirm)
5 	Processing Type 	M 	2 types of processing are supported 
1. STP 
2. NSTP 

NSTP – means that the transaction once uploaded via H2H will have to be authorized by the company on the digital platform of the bank before it gets processed. 
STP – means that the transaction once uploaded via H2H will get processed without manual authorization on the digital platform 	NSTP (Business to confirm)
6 	Customer Defined File Name 	M 	File name of customer choice for reference 	BS_<Date and Time>
7 	File Extension 	M / 3	CSV or csv 	csv

